# PagePilot – Context-Aware Browser Assistant

PagePilot is an AI-powered Chrome extension that enables users to interact with and query the content of any webpage in real time. Leveraging a custom Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pipeline, users can ask questions about research papers, technical documentation, blogs, and other knowledge-intensive webpages without manually reading the entire content.

## Features

* Extracts webpage content dynamically using Chrome Extension APIs.
* Splits large documents into context-aware chunks using `RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter`.
* Generates embeddings using `SentenceTransformers` and stores them in a `FAISS` vector index.
* Retrieves semantically relevant context for user queries through similarity search.
* Utilizes `Ollama LLaMA 3.2` via LangChain to generate context-aware responses.
* Provides a seamless chat interface directly within the browser.

## Architecture

```text
User
│
├── Chrome Extension
│       └── Extract Webpage Content
│
├── FastAPI Backend
│       ├── Text Chunking
│       ├── Embedding Generation
│       ├── FAISS Vector Store
│       └── Context Retrieval
│
└── LLaMA 3.2 (Ollama)
        └── Response Generation
```

## Tech Stack

| Component    | Technologies                               |
| ------------ | ------------------------------------------ |
| Frontend     | HTML, JavaScript, Chrome Extension APIs    |
| Backend      | Python, FastAPI                            |
| LLM          | Ollama, LLaMA 3.2                          |
| RAG Pipeline | LangChain, FAISS                           |
| Embeddings   | SentenceTransformers (`BAAI/bge-small-en`) |

## Future Improvements

* Multi-page context retention
* Citation-aware responses
* Hybrid retrieval mechanisms
* Conversation history support
* Support for additional embedding models
